<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,373,1843,1870]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Vorticella colorata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mereschkowsky, C." box="[381,654,1843,1869]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" pagination="203 - 385" refId="ref16412" refString="Mereschkowsky, C. (1877) Studies on the Protozoa of Northern Russia. Travaux de la Societe des Naturalistses a St. Petersburg, 8 (3), 203 - 385. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1877">Mereschkowsky, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1915,2014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,562,1915,1941]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Record as epibiont on cnidarians:</emphasis>
The species was described attached to hydroids from the White Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1436,1915,1941]" name="Russia" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kahl, A." box="[159,282,1951,1978]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" pagination="651 - 886" refId="ref15672" refString="Kahl, A. (1935) Wimpertiere oder Ciliata (lnfusoria), eine Bearbeitung der freilebenden und ectocommensalen Infusorien der Erde, unter Ausschluss der marinen Tintinnidae. 4. Peritricha und Chonotricha. In: Grimpe G. &amp; Wagler E. (Eds.), Die Tierwelt der Nord und Ostsee, 30, pp. 651 - 886." type="journal article" year="1935">Kahl 1935</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1430,1987,2014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1915,2014]" box="[199,1430,1987,2014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,607,1987,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Record as epibiont on other hosts:</emphasis>
The species was also found on algae from the same locality (
<bibRefCitation author="Kahl, A." box="[1294,1417,1987,2014]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" pagination="651 - 886" refId="ref15672" refString="Kahl, A. (1935) Wimpertiere oder Ciliata (lnfusoria), eine Bearbeitung der freilebenden und ectocommensalen Infusorien der Erde, unter Ausschluss der marinen Tintinnidae. 4. Peritricha und Chonotricha. In: Grimpe G. &amp; Wagler E. (Eds.), Die Tierwelt der Nord und Ostsee, 30, pp. 651 - 886." type="journal article" year="1935">Kahl 1935</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,150,248]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,150,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A." box="[327,492,150,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 57" refId="ref18801" refString="Warren, A. (1986) A revision of the genus Vorticella (Ciliophora: Peritrichida). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology, 50 (1), 1 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 18297" type="journal article" year="1986">Warren (1986)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Mereschkowsky, 1877" authorityName="Mereschkowsky" authorityYear="1877" box="[743,1219,150,176]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Vorticellidae" genus="Vorticella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="colorata">
<emphasis box="[743,956,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Vorticella colorata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mereschkowsky, C." box="[965,1219,150,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" pagination="203 - 385" refId="ref16412" refString="Mereschkowsky, C. (1877) Studies on the Protozoa of Northern Russia. Travaux de la Societe des Naturalistses a St. Petersburg, 8 (3), 203 - 385. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1877">Mereschkowsky, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<emphasis box="[1261,1429,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">nomen dubium</emphasis>
. Hence, it is not clear actually what species of genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[756,865,186,212]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Vorticellidae" genus="Vorticella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Peritrichida" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[756,865,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Vorticella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found on hydroids and algae from the White Sea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
